==English==

===Etymology===
From Japanese [[京]] (''kyō'', "capital") + [[都]] (''to'', "metropolis").

===Proper noun===
'''Kyoto'''

# A city in [[Japan]] on the island of [[Honshu]] that once served as Japan’s capital.

===Alternative spellings===
* [[Kioto]]

